deleteWorkspace(25.10)                                  deleteWorkspace(25.10)

Name
       deleteWorkspace - Deletes the specified workspace

Syntax
       deleteWorkspace

       [-help]

       -name <workspaceName>

       [-dir <directory>]

       Deletes  the  specified workspace. Use this command at any stage in the
       design flow to remove a workspace that you do not need any longer.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each deleteWorkspace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteWorkspace

       -name <workspaceName>
              Specifies the name of the workspace to be deleted.

       -dir <directory>
              Specifies the directory  from  which  the  workspace  is  to  be
              deleted.  The  default  search  order  to access directories for
              deleting workspaces is as below:

              * Current working directory

              * User home directory

Example
       The following example deletes the Test workspace from the current work-
       ing directory.

       deleteWorkspace -name Test

